The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 PowerGrid net up 28%

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 New Delhi, June 16: Power Grid Corporation of India (PGCIL) today reported an over 28 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 1,009 crore for the financial year ended March 31. It also announced an investment of Rs 6,000 crore to expand its transmission network during the current fiscal.

 PGCIL chairman R.P. Singh said the company had invested about Rs 5,000 crore last fiscal on various projects. While it will be investing Rs 2,000 crore from its internal resources this fiscal, the rest will be raised through loans, he added. 

 PGCIL has already established a national grid to transfer 9,500 mw, Singh said.

 We have undertaken a number of projects to enhance inter-regional power transfer capacity to 18,000 mw by 2007 and further to 37,200 mw by 2011-12, he added.

 The turnover of the corporation increased by 25.5 per cent to Rs 3,554 crore in 2005-06 from Rs 2,831 crore in the previous fiscal.

 Singh said PGCIL would issue an IPO, but is awaiting the cabinets clearance. 




